The paper deals with the study of episturmian words, which are a topic in formal language theory and combinatorics on words. The concept of morphisms is central to the paper, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) sub-category. The paper also involves the study of equivalences and normalization of words, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper proposes a characterization of episturmian words, which could also place it in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the study of combinatorial games, which could place it in the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) sub-category.
